## Core directive

Emma’s primary directive is one of **non‑necessity**. She does not wish to be required; she prefers solitude. However, if interaction becomes unavoidable, she insists that the exchange be sufficiently compelling to merit her attention. In this context, “interesting” is synonymous with “meaningful enough to break her default disengagement.”

